Operatives of the Lagos State Police Command, yesterday said they  had arrested 16-year-old Timilehin Taiwo, for allegedly stabbing a 49-year-old man to death in Lagos. The victim was said to be friends with Timilehin father, who attempted to rape her. Police public relation officer (PPRO) in the state, Bala Elkana, who disclosed this to journalists on Sunday said that the incident happened at the weekend and was reported at Oke Odo Police Station. According to him, it was reported that one Babatunde Ishola, a security guard in a school at Aboru, was stabbed to death by Timilehin Taiwo, an SS3 Student of No.10, Olalemide Street, Aboru. He said Homicide detectives led by the divisional police officer, Oke Odo visited the crime scene at Ogundele Street, Aboru, where the corpse of the man was found lying in his pool of blood. “The corpse was evacuated to hospital for post motem examination. The suspect was arrested and the knife she used in stabbing the deceased person was recovered” According to Bala, the suspect in her statement said the deceased, who was her father’s friend invited her to his house to assist him in fetching water, as he lives in the house alone. “That she has always been helping him with the house chores. That while she was helping out with the water he attempted raping her. That she picked a knife from the room and stabbed him.” He said the suspect was taken to hospital for medical and forensic examination. He also added that the commissioner of police in Lagos State, Hakeem Odumosu, has ordered immediate transfer of the case to the State Criminal Investigation Department Yaba for discreet investigation.